title: [SOLVED]820-2849 liquid damage no power, gpu chips get really hot
message:
got in a 820-2849,  had liquid spilled on it, primary spot i found was around the u3500 had green corrosion around this area. i replaced all the parts in the area just in case any are dead/shorting to gnd.  but i still get no power or fan. both gpu chips get very hot very fast.  i checked the voltage going to the gpu to ensure it was not getting over powered and frying and it was .76 volts so im not sure where to look next.  i do get a green light on the charger, and i ultra sonic the board after i swapped the parts out in the bad area and looked around for anything else that might be corroded or fried and did not see anything out of the norm.  any ideas?  or suggestions? 
Many thanks 
Nate

title: [SOLVED]820-2849 liquid damage no power, gpu chips get really hot
message: Shorted high side FET on GPU power supply. Q9510 probably shorted (PPBUS to GPU core) and U9500 dead. Dead GPU also possible.

title: [SOLVED]820-2849 liquid damage no power, gpu chips get really hot
message: okay what is the high side on the FET? i replaced the q9510 and u9500 and now only the nvidia chip is getting hot but slowly like its working normal. after i replaced the q9510 the fan kicks on for about 5 seconds then turns off and back on. im sure there must be a short to ground on the fet on gpu power supply like you are saying maybe? the fan spin has me hopeful haha.

title: [SOLVED]820-2849 liquid damage no power, gpu chips get really hot
message: CPU voltage dropping means it is almost working. Usually with these boards it means a GPU issue. Voltage on L9510/9560 present? No damaged caps in PCIe lines to GPU?

title: [SOLVED]820-2849 liquid damage no power, gpu chips get really hot
message:
tracing back the l9560 

Q9561 pin 5 and pin 4 0volts
q9560 pin 1,2,3 = 0 volts pin 4 0 volts, pin 5 8.4volts
u9500 pin 23=0v , 24= 4.7volts, 25=0, 26=0,

title: [SOLVED]820-2849 liquid damage no power, gpu chips get really hot
message:
okay it was the u9000. i should have swapped that out last night when i was going too haha.  the only other problem now is that when i plug it into the computer the fans do not want to spin. then i hold the power button down turn it off then power it back on and the fans kick on and everything loads and works,  what would cause it to not power on the fans when the power adapter plugs in? is this just nothing or is this something to look into? i tried an smc reset and thats how i got it to start working and then realized i could power it off and then back on and it would work. i do not have the battery in tho not sure if that can affect this but haven't seen this before.  i did just try it a few more times before posting this and it seems to be working every time now. not sure what was happening at first.
